HEADWORD: Eden
<hw>E"den</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>⟦emac⟧den</ets> delight, pleasure; also, a place of pleasure,
Eden.]</ety> <def>The garden where Adam and Eve first dwelt; hence, a
delightful region or residence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

